pageContext.claim: “And in our country, [cases are] going down. We will be seeing that even more rapidly as time goes by -- a short time.”
pageContext.analysis: Cases were declining in the U.S., but they were still higher than case counts in March and April. Moreover, the number of cases recorded daily in the U.S. continued to remain among the highest in the world. The country also still had the most cases of covid-19 anywhere in the world.
